    "desc_login": "Enter your administrator credentials to log in. Default account is admin / admin in mock mode. Use the language selector in the top-right corner to switch between English and Korean.",
    "desc_dashboard": "The dashboard provides an overview of the domain: total users, groups, computers, OUs, GPOs, domain controllers, system resources (CPU, memory, disk), service health status (LDAP, Kerberos, DNS, SMB/CIFS, Replication), and recent alerts.",
    "desc_users": "Manage Active Directory user accounts. Create, edit, delete, enable/disable, and reset passwords. Search by username, display name, or email. Filter by department or status. Export to CSV.",
    "desc_groups": "Manage AD security and distribution groups. Create groups, add/remove members, set group type (security/distribution) and scope (global/domain local/universal). Export to CSV.",
    "desc_ous": "Organizational Units (OUs) are containers for organizing users, groups, computers, and other OUs. Create a hierarchical tree structure. View child object counts and manage OU descriptions.",
    "desc_computers": "View and manage computer accounts joined to the domain. Track OS distribution, join trends, and computer status. Export to CSV.",
    "desc_gpos": "Group Policy Objects (GPOs) control configuration across the domain. Create GPOs, set status (enabled/disabled), link to OUs, and manage enforcement settings.",
    "desc_dns": "Manage DNS zones and records. View forward and reverse lookup zones. Add, edit, and delete A, SRV, NS, SOA, PTR, and CNAME records. Configure TTL values.",
    "desc_policies": "Configure domain-wide password and account lockout policies. Set minimum password length, complexity requirements, password age limits, history retention, lockout threshold, duration, and reset window.",
    "desc_logs": "View system audit events including authentication, LDAP queries, DNS lookups, Kerberos activity, replication status, and security alerts. Filter by severity (info, warning, critical) and date range. Auto-refreshes every 10 seconds.",
    "desc_settings": "View system information (app version, run mode, Python/Samba versions), domain configuration (domain name, NetBIOS, functional level, domain controllers), LDAP connection settings, and backup/restore options.",
    "desc_language": "Switch the interface language between English and Korean. The setting is saved in localStorage and persists across sessions. Available in the top bar, login page, and settings page.",
